example.para:
       If you want to completely preserve the arrays and just want to append
       them to each other, use the + operator:


<?php
$array1 = array();
$array2 = array(1 => "data");
$result = $array1 + $array2;
?>


       The numeric key will be preserved and thus the association remains.


Array
(
    [1] => data
)
